                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.443,
                                "byte_start": 89799,
                                "byte_stop": 119579,
                                "text": "I have our opinion this morning in case 06-376 Hinck v. United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 7.443,
                                "stop": 15.947,
                                "byte_start": 119579,
                                "byte_stop": 153642,
                                "text": "If you fail to pay your Federal Taxes when they are due, you will end up being liable not only for the taxes but for interest as well."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.947,
                                "stop": 33.869,
                                "byte_start": 153642,
                                "byte_stop": 225322,
                                "text": "Occasionally though, you don\u2019t find out that you should have paid taxes until some time has passed because of error or delays by the internal revenue service, in such cases the Tax Court says you can ask the IRS to abate the interest to forgive it in whole or in part."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.869,
                                "stop": 39.947,
                                "byte_start": 225322,
                                "byte_stop": 249668,
                                "text": "Now, allowing tax payers to appeal to the kindness of the IRS worked out as you might expect."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.947,
                                "stop": 55.241,
                                "byte_start": 249668,
                                "byte_stop": 310795,
                                "text": "In 1996 Congress passed the provision at issuing this case, Section 6404(h) of the tax code, which allows the tax payer to obtain judicial review of an IRS decision not to abate interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.241,
                                "stop": 61.506,
                                "byte_start": 310795,
                                "byte_stop": 335872,
                                "text": "Section 6404(h) provides that the tax court has jurisdiction over such actions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.506,
                                "stop": 77.742,
                                "byte_start": 335872,
                                "byte_stop": 400865,
                                "text": "The Fifth Circuit reasoned that District Courts and the Court Of Federal Claims have jurisdiction as well because they have general jurisdiction over tax refund claims and Section 6404(h) makes it clear that this type of claim is subject to judicial review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.742,
                                "stop": 85.724,
                                "byte_start": 400865,
                                "byte_stop": 432735,
                                "text": "The federal circuit in this case disagreed ruling that interest abatement claims could be brought only in the Tax Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.724,
                                "stop": 89.911,
                                "byte_start": 432735,
                                "byte_stop": 449453,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk today we agree with the Federal Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.911,
                                "stop": 103.51,
                                "byte_start": 449453,
                                "byte_stop": 503892,
                                "text": "We have held that a precisely drawn detailed statute preempts more general remedies and Section 6404(h) does not simply say that interest abatement claims are subject to judicial review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.51,
                                "stop": 115.925,
                                "byte_start": 503892,
                                "byte_stop": 553525,
                                "text": "It specified where such claims shall be brought and adds other features to the new remedy, such as a 180 days statute of limitations and the net worth sealing for eligible plaintiffs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.925,
                                "stop": 125.811,
                                "byte_start": 553525,
                                "byte_stop": 593126,
                                "text": "You cannot isolate one element of the statute the provision allowing review and use it to circumvent the other limitations included in the same statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.811,
                                "stop": 137.977,
                                "byte_start": 593126,
                                "byte_stop": 641714,
                                "text": "Congress plainly envisions Section 6404(h) as a package deal and one part of that package was the provision specifying that the Tax Court has jurisdiction over these actions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.977,
                                "stop": 142.576,
                                "byte_start": 641714,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We therefore affirm the judgment of the Court of Appeals, our opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
